title: Top travel photos of the week
persons: Kopczynski REUTERS/Kevin Coombs REUTERS/TOBY MELVILLE REUTERS/CARLO ALLEGRI
text:
Top travel photos of the week Last updated 09:36, October 16 2015 REUTERS/Fayaz Aziz REUTERS/China Daily REUTERS/Regis Duvignau REUTERS/Pawel Kopczynski REUTERS/Kevin Coombs REUTERS/TOBY MELVILLE REUTERS/CARLO ALLEGRI JORGE SILVA/REUTERS Adam Nurkiewicz/Getty Images Guido De Bortoli/GettyImages ILYA NAYMUSHIN/REUTERS DARRIN ZAMMIT LUPI/REUTERS BRIAN SNYDER/REUTERS JACKY NAEGELEN/REUTERS STRINGER/MEXICO KHAM/REUTERS NAVESH CHITRAKAR/REUTERS STRINGER/MEXICO PHILIMON BULAWAYO/REUTERS PAWEL KOPCZYNSKI/REUTERS PAULO WHITAKER/REUTERS 
A sailor stands on the bow of his tourist boat in the Sardaryab River at Charsadda, on the outskirts of Peshawar, Pakistan. 
A tourist poses for photographs in front of the rising sun at a tourist resort in Bayingolin Mongol Autonomous Prefecture, Xinjiang Uighur Autonomous Region, China. 
A tourist and the beach are reflected in the windows of a building near the beach at Capbreton, southwestern France. 
Tourists visit the Christ the Redeemer statue in Rio de Janeiro. 
Tourists take selfies near the Eiffel Tower in Paris. 
Tourists take photographs in front of autumn foliage in central London, Britain. 
A woman (L) who gave her name as Allyson and who is dressed up as the Statue of Liberty teases and harasses a man who is also dressed up as a Statue of Liberty while she films a comedy segment in Times Square in the Manhattan borough of New York. 
Handicraft vendor Zar Zar, 28, poses as she waits for tourists in front of the ruins of the temple Pahtodawgyi in Mingu, Myanmar. 
Queen Mathilde of Belgium and King Philippe of Belgium visit the Tomb of the Unknown Soldier as part of official Royal visit in Poland. 
Louis Boniface of France at the Red Bull Airlines and THE WALK Movie Freestyle Slackline Competition above the balconies in Catania, Sicily. 
A truck drives along the M54 "Yenisei" highway during a snowfall in the Western Sayan mountains in Southern Siberia near an administrative border with Tuva region, Russia. 
A plane leaves contrails in the sky as it flies over Malta at sunset. 
A woman pushes a baby stroller around Dream Lake amid fall foliage in Amherst, New Hampshire. 
A crucifix is seen along a road near rows of vineyards as autumn colours mark a change in season in Orschwihr in the Alsace region of France. 
A keeper holds a four-week-old jaguar while presenting it to the media, at a zoo in Ciudad Juarez, Mexico. 
Nguyen Van Huynh stands next to his winning cow during the Miss Milk Cow beauty contest in Moc Chau plateau, Vietnam. The beauty contest selects cows with solid torsos, high legs and provide the most milk. This year, 126 cows have been chosen for the contest among the 18,000 cows in Moc Chau. Miss Milk Cow beauty contest has been held at Moc Chau plateau for over a decade to promote local dairy products as the diet of Vietnamese people rapidly changed with higher income. The winner this year is a five-year-old cow that weighs 710 kg and provides around 59.6 kg milk each day, nearly triple the average amount of milk produced by Vietnam's cows. 
A man plays on a traditional swing during Dashain, the biggest religious festival for Hindus in Nepal, in Kathmandu 
A keeper feeds a four-week-old jaguar while presenting it to the media, at a zoo in Ciudad Juarez, Mexico. 
A lion wears a tracking collar as it walks inside Zimbabwe's Hwange National Park in Hwange. The park was home to country's most famous lion, Cecil, killed by US Dentist Walter Palmer in July. 
People enjoy the sunny weather at Ipanema beach in Rio de Janeiro, Brazil. 
Indigenous children from the Kamayura tribe play with balloons in Ipavu lake at Xingu national park in Mato Grosso, Brazil. The Kamayura tribe consists of around 300 people, and is one of the 16 ethnic groups living in the indigenous Xingu national park. 1 of 21 
Here is our round up of the top travel photos from around the world. 
Do you have a favourite? Let us know in the comments.
